main event: An observer sighted and attempted to photograph a gray metallic object flying in King of Prussia, Pennsylvania, on March 24, 1967.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be 50 feet away from the observer and traveling at approximately 70 mph., The sighting lasted for 33 seconds., The observer described the object as a gray metallic entity., The document indicates the photograph was likely a reflection due to the observer's glasses., The report includes a request from the observer to have their photograph returned.
witness description: A 14-year-old male who recorded the sighting and made requests related to an accompanying photograph.
